It is understood the woman was asleep when she was disturbed by a 31-year-old man on Wednesday. CAPE TOWN - Eastern Cape police have confirmed an arrest has been made in connection with a rape of an 80-year-old woman. It is understood the woman was asleep when she was disturbed by a 31-year-old man on Wednesday. The suspect attacked and raped the woman authorities say the man is to make a court appearance in the week. Captain Jackson Manatha says, “I can confirm that a 31-year-old man was arrested on Saturday for the alleged rape of an elderly woman.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)